Chelsea captain John Terry has nominated Eden Hazard for PFA Player of the Year  . 
  David de Gea and Harry Kane are also in the running for the award . 
  Jamie Carragher says Terry will have told his team-mates not to vote for the pair to give Hazard a better chance of winning . 
  Liverpool midfielder Philippe Coutinho completes the six-man shortlist . 
  Hazard is the favourite to win the award ahead of Manchester United goalkeeper De Gea . 
  Diego Costa and Alexis Sanchez are also on the list . 
 